E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20author's%20son%20and%20grandfather%20outside%20in%20a%20park.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F690380b50be9845f2dc564cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20son%20and%20grandfather%20often%20play%20together%20outside.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Autumn%20Gavora%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223bae0881-b264-4968-b416-d6dc1b753ae3%5C%22%3EThere%20are%20other%20unexpected%20perks%20to%20our%20living%20arrangement%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20laughable%20pro%20that%20I%20am%20certainly%20going%20to%20miss%20is%20having%20our%20laundry%20folded.%20My%20husband's%20grandmother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flaundry-parents-house-excuse-spend-more-time-together-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eloves%20doing%20laundry%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20chore%20I%20absolutely%20despise.%20If%20she%20hears%20the%20dryer%20running%2C%20she%20puts%20a%20timer%20on%20her%20phone%20so%20she%20can%20get%20to%20it%20as%20soon%20as%20it's%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20try%20to%20beat%20her%20to%20it%2C%20because%20I%20didn't%20want%20her%20thinking%20I%20was%20lazy%3B%20over%20time%2C%20however%2C%20I%20realized%20how%20much%20joy%20it%20gives%20her%20to%20do%20things%20for%20us%20(and%20I%20sure%20don't%20mind%20it%2C%20either).%20I%20also%20began%20to%20understand%20that%20by%20not%20letting%20her%20help%20us%2C%20it%20made%20her%20feel%20like%20we%20didn't%20need%20her.%20Allowing%20her%20to%20do%20certain%20things%20became%20a%20win-win%3B%20it%20made%20things%20easier%20for%20us%2C%20and%20showed%20her%20that%20we%20do%20need%20her%20in%20our%20lives%2C%20and%20she's%20very%20useful%20to%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20also%20greatly%20enjoyed%20splitting%20the%20cooking%20and%20enjoying%20a%20meal%20as%20a%20family.%20After%20we%20moved%20into%20my%20father-in-law's%20house%2C%20my%20husband%20has%20been%20better%20about%20leaving%20work%20at%20a%20decent%20time.%20There%20are%20now%20more%20nights%20than%20not%20when%20we%20sit%20down%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fteach-kids-teens-table-manners-dinnertime-rules-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edinner%20as%20a%20family%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20nights%20we%20don't%20talk%20much%20and%20just%20enjoy%20each%20other's%20presence%3B%20other%20times%2C%20we%20have%20dinners%20full%20of%20conversations%20about%20anything%20and%20everything.%20It's%20just%20a%20time%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20enjoy%20being%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c49bba64-ae46-4afe-9e2e-cbeaaa05342a%5C%22%3EThe%20only%20real%20con%20will%20be%20how%20much%20we'll%20miss%20living%20here%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESurprisingly%2C%20there%20aren't%20many%20cons%20of%20living%20with%20my%20husband's%20father.%20I%20may%20not%20be%20accustomed%20to%20the%20extra%20noise%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffamily-planed-to-live-in-suburbs-shares-900-sqft-apartment-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esharing%20a%20smaller%20space%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20my%20husband%20and%20toddler%2C%20but%20overall%2C%20the%20experience%20has%20been%20a%20pleasure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20biggest%20con%20of%20all%20is%20going%20to%20be%20when%20we%20go%20back%20home%2C%20and%20my%20son%20won't%20get%20to%20see%20his%20grandpa%20every%20day.%20Especially%20the%20cherished%20moments%20he%20has%20with%20his%20great-grandparents.%20Sometimes%20life%20throws%20you%20unexpected%20curveballs%20for%20reasons%20greater%20than%20you%20know%2C%20and%20I%20think%20in%20this%20case%2C%20it%20was%20to%20give%20us%20extra%20time.%20Time%20with%20our%20family%2C%20to%20remind%20us%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20reconnect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20greatest%20joys%20to%20come%20out%20of%20this%20has%20been%20the%20bond%20that%20my%20little%20one%20and